@Joya 

Yes, but I'm slightly underestimating how very much of a non-morning person I am....  Unless you consider still being up at 2 or 3 am a morning person.  Har!! 

Not doable during the work week but on the weekends, I want my breakfast and lunch options to show up around 4 pm.  I'm an odd duck that way. But not a BADEG.

@Barry Ancona 
"Maybe Framinghams?" FTW! 
Thanks for putting a big smile on my face!

@Shari Coats 

Names for two different things, usually. 
You have one skiboard on each foot, both feet on one snowboard.

@Bob T. 

Speaking of Cape ____,  I MAY have to differ! :)

@Chris Welch

Hang in there.  It gets better and better with practice.  The daily column and comments are also an excellent learning tool.

@Christina F 

Sorry, that's tough!  Don't be discouraged though, you're still making great progress, and each puzzle has it's unique level of toughness and things that may or may not be in our wheelhouses. 

Out of curiosity, how do you solve?  If on the phone app, I find that using the list view can really help pinpoint errors. You just see all the answers in a list, so don't have to navigate the grid when checking for errors.
